qr-scanner v1.4.2 (nimiq) — https://github.com/nimiq/qr-scanner

Vendored, not CDN-loaded, on purpose:
  * The template previously loaded https://unpkg.com/@AziDev/qrcodescanner/... which is a
    404 — that package does not exist on npm. wallet-scanner.js guards on
    `typeof QrCodeScanner === 'undefined'`, so the page silently showed "Camera Unavailable"
    and camera check-in never worked; only manual barcode entry did.
  * The API wallet-scanner.js was written against — new X(video, cb, {highlightScanRegion,
    highlightCodeOutline}), .start(), .stop(), result.data — is exactly nimiq/qr-scanner's.

Only qr-scanner.umd.min.js is needed: the UMD build inlines its Web Worker as a blob
(QrScanner.WORKER_PATH is explicitly "not required and not supported anymore" in 1.4.x).
